First Lady, Jill Biden, welcomed attendees to the White House and spoke about the power of sports to bring people together. She mentioned her Joining Forces initiative and shared a story about a military kid who found solace in playing soccer while stationed in Germany. Biden emphasized that sports unite people across backgrounds and borders and build confidence and resilience. She thanked Major League Soccer and Commissioner Garber for their inspiration and support. She also expressed excitement for the upcoming Women's World Cup and thanked D.C. Parks and Recreation and D.C. United for providing opportunities for young athletes. The event concluded with a ceremonial first kick by the players.